The developer is very responsive and the app is good overall. But, although you can enable/disable the app's news "Sources," such as Drudge, you cannot disable the actual news Feeds themselves. So, if you don't want to see garbage from CNN, HuffPo, or the NY Times, you'll have to shut your eyes. To me, not being able to filter these out defeats the purpose of an app that professes to be dedicated to delivering Conservative news. Tired of being subjected to it. Finally uninstalled.

content: FINALLY!!! I have been waiting for this ad free version because the ads were driving me crazy. As always, this is my goto news app. Love the clean interface and multiple news sources (especially since I have become disappointed with drudge). If you have previously paid for this app, send your paid order number to the developer (before you leave a negative review) and, hopefully, he will send you a redeem code so you will not have to pay again (that's what he did for me).
